#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int a[6][6],count;
int check(int m,int n)
{	
	if((a[m-1][n-1]==1)&&((m-1)>=0)&&((n-1)>=0))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m-1,n-1);
	}
	else if((a[m-1][n]==1)&&((m-1)>=0))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m-1,n);
	}
	else if((a[m-1][n+1]==1)&&((m-1)>=0)&&((n+1)<=5))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m-1,n+1);
	}
	else if((a[m][n-1]==1)&&((n-1)>=0))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m,n-1);
	}
	else if((a[m][n+1]==1)&&((n+1)<=5))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m,n+1);
	}
	else if((a[m+1][n-1]==1)&&((m+1)<=5)&&((n-1)>=0))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m+1,n-1);
	}
	else if((a[m+1][n]==1)&&((m+1)<=5))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m+1,n);
	}
	else if((a[m+1][n+1]==1)&&((m+1)<=5)&&((n+1)<=5))
	{	a[m][n]=0;
		count++;		
		check(m+1,n+1);
	}
	else
		return 0;
}
int main()
{	int t,i,j,flag,m,n;
	cin>>t;
	while(t--)
	{	
		flag=0;
		for(i=0;i<6;i++)
		{   for(j=0;j<6;j++)			//input
		    {	cin>>a[i][j];
		    	if((a[i][j]==1)&&(flag==0))
			{	flag=1;
				m=i;
				n=j;
					    
			}
		    }
		}
		if(flag==1)
		{	count=1;
			check(m,n);
				
				
			if(count==6)
				cout<<"correct"<<endl;
		
			else
				cout<<"incorrect"<<endl;
		}
		else
			cout<<"incorrect"<<endl;

	}
	return 0;
}
